### <span id="v.XLVII-p1.1"></span>CHAPTER XLVII.

<span id="v.XLVII-p2"></span>

<span id="v.XLVII-p3"></span>The Son is the intelligence of intelligence
and the Truth of truth

<span id="v.XLVII-p4"></span>

<span id="v.XLVII-p5"></span>BUT if the very substance of the Father is
intelligence, and knowledge, and wisdom, and truth, it is <span
id="page_110">p. 110</span> <span
id="v.XLVII-Page_110"></span>consequently inferred that as the Son is
the intelligence, and knowledge, and wisdom, and truth, of the paternal
substance, so he is the intelligence of intelligence, the knowledge of
knowledge, the wisdom of wisdom, and the truth of truth.

